main event: An unidentified flying object was observed in Hawaii on January 5, 1969, resembling a landing light at around 10 miles in altitude, rising vertically before disappearing.
interesting points: The observation lasted for 2 hours and 25 minutes., The object changed in brightness, appearing to glow and then fade., The observer was an Air Traffic Controller., The conclusion drawn from the sighting was that the object was likely planet Jupiter., The sighting involved only one confirmed witness.
sighted object: a bright round object resembling a landing light
witness description: Air Traffic Controller for five and a half years, identified as SSgt Donald E. Ellis.
